This is code associated with a pair of articles on http://codeandfootball.wordpress.com.

This Perl module implements the simple ranking system algorithm as described by Doug Drinen. 
That algorithm is described here: 

http://www.pro-football-reference.com/blog/?p=37

There are three flavors, for which we only recommend the iterative
solution for the typical user, as the actual equation tends to yield matrices that are
singular. This module requires both Math::MatrixReal and PDL to function. It is quite
raw and intended for illustrative purposes. Read the code, use it if you wish, use it
in production at your own risk.

David Myers.
